(146, 56, 'paragraph_2_who', '<div class=\"col-md-7 pt-5 mb-5\">\r\n<div class=\"kl-title-secondary kl-title-64 kl-title-arrow mx-auto\">\r\n<div class=\"kl-content-wwa-3\">\r\n<div class=\"kl-content-text kl-text-16 mt-2\">\r\n\r\nNiyel was <strong>founded in 2008</strong> by social justice advocate and policy expert Valerie G. Traore, who saw the need to <strong>boost African influence</strong> in the strategy and development space and combat the lack of agency noticed in <strong>equity initiatives on the continent and around the world.</strong> As one of the only African firms to <strong>pilot sustainable change and development,</strong> Niyel’s innovation bridges the gap between advocacy and contextual implementation. Our mission is to <strong>promote equality and trust throughout communities</strong> while amplifying the voices of everyday people. In the past 14 years, we’ve partnered with <strong>NGOs, social movements, foundations, and everything in between on over 120+ projects to date. </strong>Today, Niyel stands as a competitive global firm on its way to leading change in the progressive development and advocacy sector.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-5 mb-5 d-flex align-items-center\">\r\n<div class=\"kl-bg-wwa-blue\"></div>\r\n</div>'),
